# Certificate Upload Website

This is a simple web application for uploading certificates with user authentication and batch-wise storage. The purpose of creating this website is to help college teachers manage their certificates easily.

## Features

- User authentication: Users can register and log in with their credentials.
- Certificate upload: Users can upload certificates, which are stored in batch-wise folders.
- Batch selection: Users can select their batch from a dropdown menu when uploading certificates.

## Technologies Used

- HTML/CSS: Frontend design and layout.
- PHP: Backend server-side scripting for handling form submissions and file uploads.
- MySQL: Database management system for storing user information and certificates.
- XAMPP: Local development environment for testing.

## Setup

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/certificate-upload-website.git


1)Import the SQL file (database.sql) into your MySQL database to set up the required tables.

2)Configure your database connection details in backend.php.

3)Place the project files in your web server directory (e.g., htdocs for XAMPP).

4)Access the website through your web browser.

Usage:
Register/Login: Users can register for a new account or log in with existing credentials.
Certificate Upload: After logging in, users can upload certificates by providing necessary details including their batch.

